<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AERODYNAMIC PANELS - SLEEPER BOX AIR DEFLECTOR AND SIDE
        EXTENSIONS (93/9400)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SLEEPER BOX AIR DEFLECTOR AND SIDE EXTENSIONS (93/9400)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>REMOVE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts and washers retaining the extension assembly to the sleeper box mounting
                    brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601029">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601029" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601029" filename="../figg16/G1601029.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Sleeper Box Mounting Brackets</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1.SLEEPER BOX</callout1>
                        <callout1>2.FAIRING, SLEEPER BOX SIDE (42" AND 60" BOX)</callout1>
                        <callout1>3.CHANNEL, FAIRING MOUNTING</callout1>
                        <callout1>4.AIR DEFLECTOR SIDE EXTENSION</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen hose clamps at rear brace rods. Disconnect lower ends of rear brace rods from
                    rear mounting brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen hose clamps at front brace rods in extension assembly. Remove bolt, nut and
                    washer from lower end of the front brace rod mounting brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts at the rear of each side extension that connect to the rivnuts on the
                    top of the sleeper box side fairings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove extension subassembly from roof of sleeper box.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts retaining air deflector assembly to roof of cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air deflector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove sleeper box side air deflectors and brackets as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601029">Figure 29</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
